Package net.chaossquad.mclib.command

Klasse SubcommandCommand

java.lang.Object
net.chaossquad.mclib.command.SubcommandCommand
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
TabCompletingCommandExecutor, org.bukkit.command.CommandExecutor, org.bukkit.command.TabCompleter
public class SubcommandCommand extends Object implements TabCompletingCommandExecutor
A command that can has multiple commands as subcommands.
You can add subcommands with addSubcommand(String, SubcommandEntry).
You can remove subcommands with removeSubcommand(String).
You can set a global permission for the command in the constructor
You can set a DynamicSubcommandProvider that can provide subcommands dynamically in the constructor.
You can override onExecutionWithoutSubcommand(CommandSender, Command, String) to run code when the command is executed without subcommands.
You can override onExecutionWithoutPermission(CommandSender, Command, String, String[], String) to run code when the sender does not have the permission for the command.
You can override onExecutionWithUnknownSubcommand(CommandSender, Command, String, String[]) to run code when the given subcommand does not exist.
